==Finnish==

===Etymology===

Probably from ''[[*šāma-]]'' < Proto-Baltic ''[[*zemē]]'' ([[ground]]). Cognates include Estonian [[Soome]], Sami [[Supma]], as well as [[Sami]], [[Häme]] (Tavastia), [[hämäläinen]] (Tavastian).

